metadata.name: KAO
metadata.description:
KAO is a creation of a random shape where the position of the vertices are randomly picked using cosinus, sinus, and PI number. There are also picked based on a random noise who is generated thanks to the fxhash.

Therefore, I was able to create a chaotic visual where the color of the stroke is randomly picked in high light values using HSL colors.

This project has been created using p5.js. The name KAO refers to the chaos.

metadata.name: Spiraling
metadata.description:
Look inside of you. What do you feel? What do you say to people when they ask "How's it going?"

There are 3 variations for Spiraling. I call them phases. 

Phase 1 is the most common and has a 70% chance of occurring. This phase is typically fuzzy on the inside and slightly unstable on the outside. 

Phase 2 has a 20% chance of occurring. This phase is the most unstable. 

Phase 3 is the one shown in the preview and has a 10% chance of occurring. It is typically very zen on the inside, and slightly unstable on the outside. 

Each token generates a series of 180 circles using both random values and a noise map based on the base hash.

metadata.name: Squiggly lines
metadata.description:
8192x8192px Vanilla Js

Generative painting

The drawing is based on a unique algorithm that controls a bunch of lines painting in the canvas following polar orientation rules which change direction over time and vary colors or jump to other locations all set by several features.

Features

- Color Palette: Chinese dragon,Plant based,Flesh,Lucid,Black & White,Ukraine
- Duplication: Medium, Strong
- Jump: Often, regular, rarely
- Line Length: Short, Medium, Long
- Symmetry: Diagonal, Horizontal, Vertical
- Turning probability: Little, average, a lot
- Variation: Weak, average, strong

In live mode:

- Press [s] or [double tap] to save a 8192x8192px png
- Press [p] to replay animation

By Daniel Julià Lundgren
Barcelona, March 2022
NFT License 2.0

metadata.name: RayCasting
metadata.description:
Ray casting is the most basic of many computer graphics rendering algorithms that use the geometric algorithm of ray tracing. Ray tracing-based rendering algorithms operate in image order to render three-dimensional scenes to two-dimensional images. Geometric rays are traced from the eye of the observer to sample the light (radiance) travelling toward the observer from the ray direction. The speed and simplicity of ray casting comes from computing the color of the light without recursively tracing additional rays that sample the radiance incident on the point that the ray hit.
This series of NFT was made so that you could take an active part in the process of consuming your NFT. Go ahead, walk around.

metadata.name: Tenements
metadata.description:
"Some we see no more, Tenements of Wonder
Occupy to us though perhaps to them
Simpler are the Days than the Supposition
Leave us to presume

That oblique Belief which we call Conjecture
Grapples with a Theme stubborn as Sublime
Able as the Dust to equip its feature
Adequate as Drums
To enlist the Tomb."   (Emily Dickinson )

A moody depiction of cursed tenements in a rainy city. Anxious residents racked by fevered dreams peer out of uncertain windows, while phantoms and figments prowl the lower floors.

[Plain javascript with curated window and graffiti images generated by a neural network (VQGAN+Clip)]

metadata.name: Hotlines
metadata.description:
Hotlines by CMPLX | 2022

Mint 10 or more to receive a free physical print.

What’s in a line? 

Is a line simply a connection between point A and point B, or does it tell a story?

Explore the possibilities of minimalist composition building through line, shape, color, and texture. These elements combine to form a minimalist’s playground. What can you create? 

Compositions are created primarily through random paths superimposed upon additional visual elements and range from extremely minimalist to more chaotic depending on the hash. 

Hotlines compositions are unique and randomly produced based on your mint. 

Consisting of several composition elements including grid, color, lineweight, texture, etc. The project is designed and priced to encourage multiple mints per individual to allow for more playful arrangements to build your collection. 

Landscape / Portrait / Square are all possible per mint.

1080x720 / 720x1080 / 1080x1080

“s” to save as .png 

DM @c_mplx for physical print verification and address.

metadata.name: Untitled 1 (Animated)
metadata.description:
This is the animated version of my previous token 'Untitled 1'.
Animated time for different token varies between 6 to 17 seconds.

'Untitled 1'

It is fascinating how some simple laws can create beautiful and a large variety of outputs.
At its core, this project uses a collision detection system between a particle and a wall.
I expanded on this idea and placed some rectangles (hidden), generated some balls (particles) and let the laws of motion and symmetry take control. After a little work on how to portray the trajectories, the final piece is in front of you.
Even if you don't mint, I hope you hit refresh enough times to see the variety of the artwork.
Press 's' to save as png

metadata.name: Thinking in Color
metadata.description:
The human brain is so used to seeing faces that as long as the values (light vs dark) of a face are accurate, the color used to portray those values (the chroma or hue) don't matter. 

This is my way of showing that - by using the exact same light and shadow patterns, but using different hues - every mint should read the same: a woman, eyes closed, with her hand on her face, being lit by a light source in front and in back of her. 

Each color pattern has equal rarity - will the composition break down when certain complementary color combinations create greater disharmony, or will the rigidity of the value patterns hold together regardless? 

This token marks my final mint on the fx(hash) beta contract, and was created thanks to PureSpider's template for layer-based generative projects.

metadata.name: Pebbles
metadata.description:
Generative series in six different ranges of 30 colors each that are combined with 150 colors forming a wall. "The Pebbles" series pays tribute to these first ancestral wall constructions in dry stone without concrete to hold them together. It is an ancient technique that dates back to the Stone Age.

This series of generatives NFTs is born from the drawings presented in Milan at the Galería Patricia Armocida. They are composed of stone blocks in 6 series of 50 originals in which 30 colors per range are combined with 150 secondary range colors in infinite shapes.

http://www.nuriamora.com/serie-piedras/

The first Range is Blue.


Coded in P5js.

Source code based on Roni Kaufman previous work and used under a collaborative agreement.
